  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Milano is right on the edge of the lake near the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/33b4c55b3392440f89f87098676e852a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/33b4c55b3392440f89f87098676e852a}" title="Maderno">Maderno</a> – a peaceful town on the west of the lake. It looks out over the promenade, making it nice starting point to take leisurely walks in the afternoon. A ferry port is 200 metres away so you can easily reach towns like <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva">Riva</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b}" title="Desenzano">Desenzano</a> too.</p>
<p>This is a family-run hotel and feels very relaxed with comfy rooms and good amenities. Breakfast in the ‘winter garden’ is a great way to start the day and in the summer, you can take it on the terrace next to the lake. The pool is next to the lake too and loungers are set on the manicured lawn under trees. It’s a lovely place to spend the day if you don’t fancy heading out.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 30 mins by coach from Verona airport.</p>]]></description>
